  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0152">
<l>auveṉa varūu muyiriṟu collum</l>
<l>ñanamava veṉṉum puḷḷi yiṟutiyuṅ</l>
<l>kuṟṟiya lukarat tiṟutiyu muḷappaṭa</l>
<l>muṟṟat tōṉṟā muṉṉilai moḻikkē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If [the standing word is] a verb in the second</l>
<l>person<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">muṉṉilaik kiḷavi.</foreign></note> ending in a vowel or in a consonant<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">uyirīṟu</foreign> ' vocalic Auslaut ' ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">puḷḷiyīṟu</foreign> ' consonantal Auslaut '.</note></l>
<l>[and] a plosive [at the beginning of the coming word]</l>
<l>follows, there are two alternatives possible -</l>
<l>either there is no change, or there is optional multiplication.<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">naṭakoṟṟā ~ naṭakkōṟṟa, īrkoṟṟā &amp; īrkoṟṟā;</foreign> optional multiplication = <foreign xml:lang="ta">ūraḻpu</foreign> (comm. <foreign xml:lang="ta">perukkam).</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
